festival.introText:
The exciting festival returns to Maidstone's Mote Park on Saturday 5th August 2023, featuring some of the UK's best tribute performances, celebrating artists from both past and present.

Rock The Mote will be the next best thing to the original artists at a fraction of the cost, with stadium staging, sound, light and production - a day not to be missed.

An incredible day filled with a range of genres including tributes to Fleetwood Mac, Fall Out Boy, AC/DC, Guns N' Roses, Dolly Parton, Lionel Richie, Dua Lipa, David Bowie, Whitney Houston and introducing an all NEW stage 'Thunder Dome' Featuring heavy rock tributes to Aerosmith, Black Sabbath, Iron Maiden, Metallica & more...


DJ performances, a beer, cider and ale village, street food, cocktail vendors and fairground rides.

reviews.title: Review of Rock The Mote 2022
reviews.body:
Would have been nice to have seating as we had to go home after an hour
Impression given plenty of seating!

reviews.title: Review of Rock The Mote 2022
reviews.body: Prices were extortionate, not worth the money. A baguette cost 10, Mac n cheese 8 which tasted as good as a ready meal from Tesco. Drinks were a rip off, 3 for a can of soft drink. 4 for a coffee and wasnt allowed to bring a camping stove when camping. Im sure the excuse would be fire risk but smoking was freely permitted. Free water tap wasnt connected to start with. Toilets on campsite were a disgrace, intermittent water supply.

reviews.title: Review of Rock The Mote 2022
reviews.body: Bands were great. Layout of the stages was a bit odd. Hard Rock stage should have been bigger. Prices were an out an out rip off though and the cashless token system is a total con to get you to over spend. Tokens are non-refundable and you have to buy in multiples of 10. No reason for that other than to get you to inevitably buy more than you need to save extra trips to the token tent when you're just 2 tokens short. They say its to reduce queues at vendors but having normal contactless payments would do that. Not a bad day out but the scam tokens and rip off prices leave a nasty taste. If I go again I'll get creative and sneak in my own food and drink

reviews.title: Review of Rock The Mote 2022
reviews.body: I can completely say I understand why no cooking equipment in this weather,  but it really does affect my budget for the weekend, especially as we were told we couldn't take our cars our to the shops etc. Other than that I had the best weekend. Lx

reviews.title: Review of Rock The Mote 2022
reviews.body: great event, music, food all spot on. just seemed tad expensive for drinks. but overall great time

reviews.title: Review of Rock The Mote 2022
reviews.body: Really good time for the family but ridiculous prices

reviews.title: Review of Rock The Mote 2022
reviews.body: really good shame some of the bands clashed though as wanted to see both rock and metal, Some kind of Mettallica and Led Zep deserved to be on the big stage!

faqs.question: Can we camp?
faqs.answer:
Yes, camping tickets are available from our ticket page. Please note, you can only camp with Rock The Moat,

 

if you’re in possession of a full weekend ticket.

faqs.question: Is there parking provided?
faqs.answer: Yes, parking tickets are available from their ticket page.

faqs.question: What will be there?
faqs.answer:
The event will consist of arena standard staging, lighting and sound, as well as numerous

 

fully licensed bars and street food vendors.

faqs.question: Are there any disabled tickets?
faqs.answer:
Yes, disabled customers are required to purchase a ticket and then send the confirmation, as well

as a photo/copy of their DLA/PIP letter to info@rockthemote.com. We will then process the

documents and provide them with a carer ticket free of charge.

faqs.question: How do i get to Rock the Mote?
faqs.answer:
TRAVELING BY CAR

If you’re looking to arrive by car, you will need to park in one of the many local car parks.

Click here for locations. 

 

Alternatively, if you wish to leave your vehicle overnight, we would recommend the car park

situated on Brunswick Street (maximum 24 hour stay). 

 

The car park situated within Mote Park’s main entrance is for park users only. 

 

Please note, we strongly advise that you do not park in and around residential areas surrounding

the park and doing so will run the risk of you receiving a parking ticket. 

 

TRAVELING BY TRAIN

Maidstone West Station – 1.3 miles from Mote Park 

 

Maidstone Barracks Station – 1.7 miles from Mote Park 

 

Maidstone East Station – 1.4 miles from Mote Park 

 

TRAVELING BY BUS

 

The Mall Bus Station is located approximately one mile from Mote Park.

faqs.question: Where is Rock The Mote Festival located in mote park?
faqs.answer:
The main festival entrance will be situated opposite Mote Park Café, with Mote Park’s main

 

entrance off Mote Avenue being the best way to access the site.

faqs.question: Is there disabled parking?
faqs.answer: There will be parking available for disabled customers in Mote Park’s over-flow car park.

faqs.question: Can we leave and re-enter?
faqs.answer: You unfortunately cannot leave and re-enter the event.

faqs.question: Will there be a disabled viewing area?
faqs.answer:
Unfortunately there will not be a specific disabled viewing area, however please show your

blue badge upon arrival and their marshals will do their best to locate you as close to the stage as possible.

faqs.question: Is it safe?
faqs.answer:
Each customer will be searched and so too will their bags. There will be a zero tolerance approach

 

implemented by our experienced and professional security team. 

 

All food, drinks (500ml of sealed bottled water is permitted), glass and sharp objects will be

confiscated upon entry. We ask that you do not bring perfume or any other valuable cosmetics to the event

because it will be confiscated and there is no guarantee that you will get it back. We take no responsibility for

any lost valuables at the entrance or inside the event. 

 

There will also be a medical area on site, where trained first-aiders and paramedics

will be available at any time.

faqs.question: What happens is there is bad weather?
faqs.answer:
The weather shouldn’t affect the festival too much because of the time of year, however, the ground

may become wet and soft, so if the weather up to and including the day of the festival is wet,

 

we would advise wearing your wellies and waterproof jackets!

faqs.question: Will there be disabled toilets?
faqs.answer: Yes, there will be numerous disabled toilets on site.

faqs.question: Tokens
faqs.answer:
DO I HAVE TO PURCHASE TOKENS FOR FOOD AND DRINK?

Yes, Rock The Moat event site is completely cashless, which means you will have to purchase tokens

 

for both food and drink at the event. 

 

HOW MANY TOKENS DO I NEED?

This depends on how much food and drink you intend to buy, however you can purchase

extra tokens throughout the event, should you need more. 

 

There will be token booths where you can purchase tokens situated throughout the event site

 

but please note, these tokens must be purchased in denominations of £10.00. 

 

WHAT DO I DO WITH ANY EXTRA TOKENS?

Unfortunately all tokens are non-refundable and therefore we ask that you only purchase what

you intend to spend at the event (all tokens must be purchased in £10.00 denominations). 

 

HOW CAN I PURCHASE TOKENS?

You can purchase your tokens on the day with both cash and card. 

 

WHY IS IT TOKENS ONLY?

After using tokens at a number of our events last year, we found that using tokens for food

and drink significantly speeds up service, which results in more time for you all to enjoy the event

and less time queueing for food and drinks. 

 

When purchasing food/drink with cash, staff will take money, get your items, go to the till and

count your change out and then return with your items and change, which take on

average 2/3 minutes. With tokens, this is dramatically sped up, with tokens being taken and items

 

being passed to the customer, which takes around 20/30 seconds. 

 

Our token system also minimises the risk of COVID-19 transmission. 

 

For full FAQ's please visit: https://rockthemote.com/faqs

faqs.question: When is Rock the Mote 2023?
faqs.answer: Saturday 5 - Sunday 6 August, 2023

reviewsDisplayFour.title: Review of Rock The Mote 2022
reviewsDisplayFour.body:
Fantastic day with great acts and a great carnival atmosphere. Great to see everyone enjoying themselves. 
The only thing I would suggest is the tokens should be sold in
5 not 10. 
The food was top quality, good choice, no queues, prices are reasonable and the beer prices were 6 - 7 a pint. 
Overall, a great day had by all and highly recommended.
